      "content": "thanks for the info. the taiwan/kosovo comparison is actually really helpful. the thing is, the documents i have include a signed treaty from 1954 that explicitly outlines the succession rights for the Khovd-Zorig line in case of \"administrative annexation.\" it's not just a family story, it's a documented legal obligation that was violated. if i can prove the annexation was illegal under the treaties of that era, doesn't that give me a much stronger standing for a claim at the UN or even the ICJ? how would a court look at a treaty that was suppressed by a superpower?",
